{"heading":"The people of Israel are apostate, rebellious, and corrupt; only a few remain faithful—The people’s sacrifices and feasts are rejected—They are called upon to repent and work righteousness—Zion will be redeemed in the day of restoration.","number":1,"verseCount":31,"verses":[[1,["The ",["vision",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Vision","tg/vision"],"."]]]," of ",["Isaiah",["study-note-ref","b",[["1 Ne. 19:23 (23–24)","bofm/1-ne/19.23"],"; ",["3 Ne. 23:1","bofm/3-ne/23.1"],"."]]]," the son of Amoz, which he saw concerning ",["Judah",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Israel, Judah, People of","tg/israel-judah-people-of"],"."]]]," and Jerusalem in the days of ",["Uzziah",["study-note-ref","d",[["2 Kgs. 15:13 (1–13)","ot/2-kgs/15.13"],"; ",["Hosea 1:1","ot/hosea/1.1"],"."]]],", ",["Jotham",["study-note-ref","e",[["2 Kgs. 15:30, 38 (13–38)","ot/2-kgs/15.30,38"],"; ",["Micah 1:1","ot/micah/1.1"],"."]]],", ",["Ahaz",["study-note-ref","f",[["2 Kgs. 16:20 (19–20)","ot/2-kgs/16.20"],"."]]],", ",["and",["clarity-word"]]," Hezekiah, kings of Judah."]],[2,[["Hear",["study-note-ref","a",[["Deut. 32:1","ot/deut/32.1"],"; ",["D&C 1:1 (1–2)","dc-testament/dc/1.1"],"; ",["76:1","dc-testament/dc/76.1"],"."]]],", O heavens, and give ear, O earth: for the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," hath spoken, I have nourished and brought up children, and they have ",["rebelled",["study-note-ref","b",[["Deut. 32:19","ot/deut/32.19"],"."]]]," against me."]],[3,["The ox knoweth his owner, and the ass his master’s ",["crib",["study-note-ref","a",["HEB stall or manger."]]],": ",["but",["clarity-word"]]," Israel doth not ",["know",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Apostasy of Israel","tg/apostasy-of-israel"],"; ",["God, Knowledge about","tg/god-knowledge-about"],"; ",["Ignorance","tg/ignorance"],"."]]],", my people doth not consider."]],[4,["Ah ",["sinful",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Man, Natural, Not Spiritually Reborn","tg/man-natural-not-spiritually-reborn"],"."]]]," nation, a people laden w